route_fix_signoff_drc(25.10)                      route_fix_signoff_drc(25.10)

Name
       route_fix_signoff_drc - Fixes sign-off DRC

Syntax
       route_fix_signoff_drc

       [-help]

       [-fix_rule <ruleName> | -exclude_rule <ruleName>]

       Fixes sign-off DRC. It fixes third party DRC violations which cannot be
       detect  by  the Innovus verification tool (like verify_drc).  The third
       party markers need to be converted with  the  loadViolationReport  com-
       mand.  The  supported  drc  types  include, spacing, mincut, colorLoop,
       area, minhole, maxstackedvia, enclosure, width, and minstep.

Parameters
       -exclude_rule <ruleName>
              Specifies the sign_off tool rule type to exclude.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -fix_rule <ruleName>
              Specifies the sign_off tool rule type to fix.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each route_fix_signoff_drc parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command

               man route_fix_signoff_drc    .

Related Information
              * loadViolationReport

              * Using the NanoRoute Router chapter in the Innovus User Guide

